description: 听独白，根据独白的内容，从下面各题所给的选项中选择最佳选项。录音听两遍。

content.contentDesc: My parents took me to Disneyland Park last Saturday because it was my birthday. It was really a wonderful trip and we had a wonderful time there. The cartoon characters, like Snow White, Donald Dark, brought us a lot of fun. They are smart. The roller coaster made me excited. But my parents said it made them uncomfortable. The food in the Disneyland dining hall was delicious. I liked it very much.

description: 听对话，将表格所缺的关键信息填写在相应位置上。录音听两遍。

content.content:
Travelling
Where to travel_____.
Time to travel there_____.
The weather there_____.
Travel with whom_____.
The most famous placeTerra-cotta Warriors and Horses _____.
content.contentDesc:
M: Hi, Jenny. Did you have fun on your vacation?

W: Yes, I did. I went to Xi'an with my brother.

M: How did you like it?

W: Everything was really interesting. Terra-cotta Warriors and Horses Museum is the most famous place of interest. It was built by the first emperor of China, Yingzheng. And the warriors and horses are all made of china and clay. The food in Xi'an is also wonderful. The weather there in spring is neither too cold nor too hot. You won't feel disappointed if you go there.

M: Yes, I also like the museum. And I wish to go there some day.

answers.answer: Neither too cold nor too hot
subAnswers: Neither too cold nor too hot

answerList: Neither too cold nor too hot

answers: Neither too cold nor too hot

description: 听一段短文，请根据短文内容记录关键信息。短文将听两遍。现在你有1分钟的时间浏览提示信息。

content.content:
Tom's experience

He got a _____from the police

Now he is _____.

The police had found his lost _____.

They were sending it to his home by _____.

He lost it _____years ago.
content.contentDesc: Tom was worried all week. He got a letter from the police. They told him to go to the police station as soon as he received the letter. Tom went to the police station yesterday, and now he is happy. At the police station, a smiling policeman told him that they had found his lost bike. Now they were sending it to his home by train. Tom was very surprised when he heard the news. He never expected he should find the lost bike. He lost it twenty years ago when he was a boy of fifteen.
